The Raider Operatives have arrested a suspect, Sajor Louis with 91 wraps of weeds suspected to be Indian hemp, 124 wraps of loud, 50 parcels of SK, some razlers and some bottles of liquid mixed with a substance suspected to be Indian hemp in Asaba, the Delta State capital. The suspect was arrested by the Police during a raid on black spots in Asaba. The Delta State Police Command led by CP Ari Muhammed Ali confirmed the report in a statement signed by the Police Public Relations Officer, DSP Bright Edafe. The police image maker said investigation is ongoing.